Boil your #kettle{}.

Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}. Halve lengthways and slice into
half moons.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} into half moons.

Put a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add the
@British beef mince{250%g}. Cook until browned, ~{5%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{}
to break it up as it cooks.

Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}.

Add the courgette, onion, @dried thyme{1%tsp} and @easy garlic{1}. Cook,
stirring frequently until everything softens, ~{4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiling water from your kettle into a #large saucepan{} with
a pinch of salt. Put it on high heat.

Add the @wheat spaghetti{200%g} to the boiling water and cook until 'al dente',
about ~{10%minutes}.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of
> firmness left in the middle.

Once the veggies have softened add the @diced tomatoes with basil{1%400g can}
and @Worcester sauce{1}. Simmer on medium heat until the ragu thickens,
~{7%minutes}.

> Add a glug of red wine to the ragu if you have some, it will add a great depth
> of flavour!

Drain the pasta in a #colander{} and toss it in the ragu before serving in
#bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Buon appetito!